      "attribution": "<div>Card design, game layout, and coding by LawDawg. Released to the Public Domain under CC0.</div><div><br></div><div>The pepperoni and mushroom are by ASTRAJA and are available under the Pixabay License at: https://pixabay.com/vectors/salami-pepperoni-pizza-food-5517398/ and&nbsp;https://pixabay.com/vectors/mushroom-vegetable-slice-pizza-5517458/.</div><div><br></div><div>The library image (and reset button) is by MissKaLem and available under the Pixabay License at:&nbsp;https://pixabay.com/vectors/pizza-food-slice-cartoon-cutout-8882163/</div><div><br></div><div>The background image was generated by ChatGPT 4o using the prompt: \"1600x1000 image of pizza ingredients on a counter in a kitchen including flour, salt, tomatoes, cheese, and garlic.\"</div><div><br></div><div>The bag image is by mousewax and is in the Public Domain.</div>",
      "lastUpdate": 1750864488165,
      "showName": true,
      "skill": "",
      "description": "Rival chefs race to claim the best ingredients on a shared pizza. Align three toppings in a row while blocking the opponent's culinary combos.",
      "similarImage": "",
      "similarName": "Tic Tac Trek",
      "similarDesigner": "Trevor Benjamin, Brett J. Gilbert",
      "similarAwards": "",
      "ruleText": "",
      "helpText": "<div><b>Setup</b></div><div><br></div>Sit in seats. Click reset button to begin. The two starting tiles will appear. Choose a player to go first.<div><br></div><div><b>Tiles</b></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2</div><div>Dough&nbsp; &nbsp;Herbs&nbsp; &nbsp;Sauce&nbsp; Cheese&nbsp; &nbsp;Pan</div><div><br></div><div><a href=\"/assets/-1722122116_3856\"><img src=\"/assets/-1722122116_3856\" class=\"floating richtextAsset\"></a></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>Gameplay</b></div><div><br></div><div>Take turns dragging tiles from the bag and playing them on the board. The tile being played will automatically flip to show your topping. (Click the tile to change the topping, if necessary.)</div><div><br></div><div>Play the tile orthogonally adjacent to another tile with the matching color or next to the silver tile. The silver tile is wild and can be matched with any of the other colors. If there is no matching color tile or silver tile, place the drawn tile adjacent to any other tile.</div><div><br></div><div>Drag the entire board by clicking and dragging in an area without tiles.</div><div><br></div><div>When you get 3 tiles with your topping in a row (horizontally, vertically, or diagonally), move one of your toppings onto the tile played that turn. If you make multiple 3-in-a-rows in the same play, only use one topping.</div><div><br></div><div>If you make more than six 3-in-a-row plays, you must move one of your previously placed toppings onto the tile drawn that turn. The tile you took your topping from cannot be used to make any more 3-in-a-row lines.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>End of game and scoring</b></div><div><br></div><div>When all tiles are played, record the score using the indicators near the seat. For each topping placed on the board, a player gets 1 point for each surrounding space around that topping without a tile. This can range from 0-7 points for each topping.</div><div><br></div><div>The highest score wins. In case of a tie, the most toppings played wins. If the game is still tied, the player that did not play the last tile wins.</div>",
